Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setSelectedPtnFeedthrough(25.10)              setSelectedPtnFeedthrough(25.10)

Name
       setSelectedPtnFeedthrough  -  Sets the area, name, and layer ID for the
       selected partition routing feedthrough object

Syntax
       setSelectedPtnFeedthrough

       [-help]

       <x1><y1><x2><y2>

       <PtnFeedthroughName>

       { <layerID> | <layerIDList> }

       Sets the area, name, and layer ID for the  selected  partition  routing
       feedthrough object.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each setSelectedPtnFeedthrough parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man setSelectedPtnFeedthrough

       <x1> <y1> <x2> <y2>
              Specifies the coordinates of the routing feedthrough area.

       <PtnFeedthroughName>
              Specifies the name of the routing feedthrough.

       <layerID> | <layerIDList>
              Specifies  the  metal layer(s) that can route through the parti-
              tion feedthrough.

Example
              * The following command sets the routing feedthrough object, pt-
                nFeedthru2, to allow routing on the layer 5 (Metal5) to  cross
                over the specified area:

                setSelectPtnFeedthrough 100.0 100.0 150.0 150.0 ptnFeedthru2 5

